data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.ActiveWriterDomainModel.Description
data.value: A Visual Studio 2010 addin to design domain models and to generate code decorated with ActiveRecord attributes or supported with NHibernate configuration based on the model.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/UseNullables.Description
data.value: Instructs ActiveWriter to generate code using nullables where possible.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/CaseOfPrivateFields.Description
data.value: Tells ActiveWriter how to name private fields of properties if the Access of Property is PropertyAccess.Property (Default)

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/GenerateMonoRailProject.Description
data.value: Tells ActiveWriter to generate a seperate MonoRail project with View and Controller code, taking this file's output as the model.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/MonoRailProjectName.Description
data.value: Name of the MonoRail project. If a project with the same name already exists in the solution, it won't be added to the solution.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/UseGenerics.Description
data.value: Instructs ActiveWriter to generate code using generic bases where possible. This setting is overridable in class level.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/UseBaseClass.Description
data.value: Instructs ActiveWriter to generate classes inherited from a base class. If Base Class Name property is empty, ActiveRecordBase or ActiveRecordBase<T> will be used depending on the Use generics property.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/BaseClassName.Description
data.value: Defines the base class to be inherited. Does have no effect if Use Base Class property is set to false.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/GeneratesDoubleDerived.Description
data.value: If true, will generate a base class with all functionality and a derived partial class to support customization through overrides.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/DoubleDerivedNameSuffix.Description
data.value: Suffix appended to base class names in double derived code generation. Defaults to "Base", if not supplied.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/UseGeneratedCodeAttribute.Description
data.value: Instructs ActiveWriter to decorate each class with GeneratedCodeAttribute. Some tools evaluate existance of this attribute to handle code differently.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/Target.Description
data.value: Defines the experimental code generation target.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/AssemblyPath.Description
data.value: Provides assembly load path for Castle.ActiveRecord.dll and related assemblies. If required assemblies are in GAC, this setting is omitted. If not and is this setting is blank, or required assemblies not found under the given path if they are not in the GAC, an error will be thrown during code generation.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/ActiveRecordAssemblyName.Description
data.value: Provides assembly name to be used during code generation. You can provide a fully qualified assembly name to target a specific version from the GAC.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/NHibernateAssemblyName.Description
data.value: Provides assembly name to be used during code generation. You can provide a fully qualified assembly name to target a specific version from the GAC.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/RelateWithActiwFile.Description
data.value: Instructs ActiveWriter to add hbm.xml file as a nested file of this .actiw file. Otherwise, file will be added as a standalone item to the project.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/UseVirtualProperties.Description
data.value: Instructs ActiveWriter to generate virtual properties where possible.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/Namespace.Description
data.value: The namespace to be used in generated code. If not supplied (default), ActiveWriter will use the namespace from the native project structure.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/AdditionalImports.Description
data.value: List of additional imports to be added to the generated class.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/ImplementINotifyPropertyChanged.Description
data.value: Instructs ActiveWriter to implement INotifyPropertyChanged interface in each class generated. This setting is overridable in class level.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/GenerateMetaData.Description
data.value: Instructs ActiveWriter to generate property metadata to allow typed access to property names.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/UseNHQG.Description
data.value: Instructs ActiveWriter to post process generated code with NHibernate Query Generator to generate helper Criteria API constructs. For more information on NHQG, visit http://www.ayende.com

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/UseGenericRelations.Description
data.value: Instructs ActiveWriter to generate code using generic collections for class relations where possible. This setting is overridable in class level.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/PropertyNameFilterExpression.Description
data.value: A regular expression to apply to all property names. MAtches will bereplaced with empty strings.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/InitializeIListFields.Description
data.value: Initializas private IList fields with List concrete type.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/ImplementINotifyPropertyChanging.Description
data.value: Instructs ActiveWriter to implement INotifyPropertyChanging interface in each class generated. This setting is overridable in class level.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/CollectionInterface.Description
data.value: Interface to use for collections. If none is specified, IList will be used.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/CollectionImplementation.Description
data.value: Concrete class to instantiate for list fields if InitializeIListFields is set to true.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/ManyToManyRelationType.Description
data.value: Default relation type used by ManyToMany relationships.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/ManyToOneRelationType.Description
data.value: Default relation type used by ManyToOne relationships.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/ManyToManyCollectionIDColumnFormat.Description
data.value: This column name is used for many to many collection ID definition. If a column name is specified in the relationship itself, the Column Type and Generator specified in the relationship will be used instead of those specified here in the model. Any {0} specified in the format will be replaced with the table name in the same way as Common Primary Key Format. If no format is specified here or in the many to many relationships, the generation system will fall back to the Common Primary Key information.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/ManyToManyCollectionIDColumnFormat.DisplayName
data.value: Many To Many Collection ID Column Format

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/ManyToManyCollectionIDColumnType.Description
data.value: Description for Castle.ActiveWriter.Model.Many To Many Collection ID Column Type

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/ManyToManyCollectionIDColumnType.DisplayName
data.value: Many To Many Collection ID Column Type

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/ManyToManyCollectionIDGenerator.Description
data.value: Description for Castle.ActiveWriter.Model.Many To Many Collection ID Generator

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/ManyToManyCollectionIDGenerator.DisplayName
data.value: Many To Many Collection ID Generator

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/ManyToManyIUserCollectionType.Description
data.value: The type deriving from NHibernate.UserTypes.IUserCollectionType for collections. This is used unless the collection type is specified in the ManyToMany relationship.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/ManyToOneIUserCollectionType.Description
data.value: The type deriving from NHibernate.UserTypes.IUserCollectionType for collections. This is used unless the collection type is specified in the ManyToOne relationship.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/AutomaticAssociationCollectionImplementation.Description
data.value: Description for Castle.ActiveWriter.Model.Automatic Association Collection Implementation

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/ManyToManyTableFormat.Description
data.value: The format used by default for many-to-many table names. {0} is replaced by the source class name and {1} is replaced by the target class name.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/ForeignKeyFormat.Description
data.value: The format string used by default for foreign key relationships. {0} is replaced with the property or class name. A common format string might be: {0}_ID

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/CommonPrimaryKeyPropertyFormat.Description
data.value: If no other primary key is specified, a primary key will be generated with this format. {0} will be replaced with the class name. As an example, {0}Id would generate SomeClassId as the primary key property for SomeClass. If left blank, no primary keys will be added to classes without existing primary keys.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/CommonPrimaryKeyColumnFormat.Description
data.value: The column name used for the common primary key property. If not specified, the name of the property will be used. {0} will be replaced with the name of the table. For example, you could use the table name with a standard suffix: {0}_ID

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/CommonPrimaryKeyColumnType.Description
data.value: NHibernate type for common primary key.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/CommonPrimaryKeyGenerator.Description
data.value: Generator type for common primary key.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/MemberTemplateFile.Description
data.value: Methods and propeties from the single class within the template file will be imported, transformed, and then placed in the generated output. As an example, you could specify the ActiveRecordBase.Generic.cs file and the generic methods would be transformed into specific methods for each class. The first generic type parameter is replaced with the generated class type. There are additional transformations for subclasses. The path to the source file is relative to the .actiw file. If the path has "..." in it, all parent folders are searched upwards until a match is found. For example, "...\ActiveRecord\ActiveRecordBase.generic.cs" would look for "ActiveRecord\ActiveRecordBase.generic.cs" in the folder containing the .actiw file and in all folders up to the root.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/BaseClassPropertyChangedMethod.Description
data.value: If there is already a PropertyChanged event defined in the base class, specify the name of a method that takes a single string that can be used to invoke it.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/BaseClassPropertyChangingMethod.Description
data.value: If there is already a PropertyChanging event defined in the base class, specify the name of a method that takes a single string that can be used to invoke it.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.Model/Access.Description
data.value: Global property access setting. Can be overridden at class or property level.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.ModelClass/DiscriminatorColumn.Description
data.value: Discriminator column for a table inheritance modeling

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.ModelClass/DiscriminatorType.Description
data.value: Column type (like string or integer) for the discriminator column

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.ModelClass/DiscriminatorValue.Description

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.ModelClass/Lazy.Description
data.value: Enable lazy loading for the type

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.ModelClass/Proxy.Description
data.value: Associates a proxy type with the target type

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.ModelClass/Schema.Description
data.value: Schema name associated with the type

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.ModelClass/Table.Description
data.value: Table name associated with the type

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.ModelClass/DynamicInsert.Description
data.value: Specifies that INSERT SQL should be generated at runtime and contains only the columns whose values are not null.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.ModelClass/DynamicUpdate.Description
data.value: Specifies that UPDATE SQL should be generated at runtime and contains only those columns whose values have changed.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.ModelClass/SelectBeforeUpdate.Description
data.value: Specifies that NHibernate should never perform an SQL UPDATE unless it is certain that an object is actually modified. In certain cases (actually, only when a transient object has been associated with a new session using update()), this means that NHibernate will perform an extra SQL SELECT to determine if an UPDATE is actually required.

data.value: Determines whether implicit or explicit query polymorphism is used.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.ModelClass/Mutable.Description
data.value: Specifies that instances of the class are (not) mutable.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.ModelClass/BatchSize.Description
data.value: Specify a "batch size" for fetching instances of this class by identifier.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.ModelClass/UseAutoImport.Description
data.value: The auto-import attribute lets us use unqualified class names in the query language, by default. The assembly and namespace attributes specify the assembly where persistent classes are located and the namespace they are declared in.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.ModelClass/BaseClassName.Description
data.value: If set and if model level base class usage is set, overrides any base class defined in the model.

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.ModelClass/UseGenerics.Description

data.name: Castle.ActiveWriter.ModelClass/UseGenericRelations.Description
